3. cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction): The paper proposes using FMCW radar as an interacting interface on a laptop, which involves designing a user-friendly interface and falls under the domain of human-computer interaction. 
4. cs.MM (Multimedia): The paper deals with processing and analyzing signals from FMCW radar, which can be considered as a form of multimedia. 
5. cs.SD (Sound): Although the paper does not explicitly deal with sound, FMCW radar uses radio waves which can be considered as a form of sound, and the paper involves processing and analyzing these signals.
